# {{projectName}}

{{description}}

A production-ready TypeScript CLI built with Commander.js and chalk.

## What you need to modify

Your project has 7 files. You only need to care about 2:

| File | What it does | When to edit |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| `src/index.ts` | All your CLI commands live here | **Every time** |
| `tests/index.test.ts` | Tests for your commands | **Every time** |
| `package.json` | Dependencies + scripts | Only when adding packages |
| `tsconfig.json` | TypeScript config | Almost never |
| `eslint.config.mjs` | Linting rules | Almost never |
| `README.md` | This file | Before publishing |
| `AGENTS.md` | AI assistant instructions | Only if changing conventions |

## Quick Start

```bash
npm install
npm run dev -- json package.json   # format this file as JSON
npm run dev -- count "hello world" # count words
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── index.ts          # Entry point, Commander setup, all commands
tests/
├── index.test.ts     # Integration tests (subprocess execution)
```

## Commands

| Command | Arguments | Description |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| `json` | `<file>` (required) | Read and format a JSON file |
| `count` | `<text>` (required) | Count characters and words |

## Scripts

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm run dev -- <args>` | Dev mode with hot reload |
| `npm run build` | Compile to `dist/` |
| `npm start -- <args>` | Run compiled binary |
| `npm test` | Run tests |
| `npm run test:watch` | Watch mode tests |

## Stack

- **Runtime**: Node.js + TypeScript (ESM)
- **CLI framework**: Commander.js (argument parsing, subcommands, help)
- **Testing**: Vitest (CLI integration tests via execSync)
